<taxonomicName id="7F159A0F1AA2F2FF399AC5EA73480C7D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sarrachoides" order="Solanales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sarrachoides">
<emphasis id="33236D9BCD836829171C28BED93101C8" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Solanum sarrachoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to southern South America, and is sporadically introduced to North America, where it is much less common than the morphologically similar 
<taxonomicName id="35F7C8E2705F416C0D5F44D6E3C09F81" family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. nitidibaccatum" order="Solanales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="nitidibaccatum">
<emphasis id="6B5D3D926E4FAF52729A303BB1EE9A08" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">S. nitidibaccatum</emphasis>
